The test failed. The actual output uses the copy constructor (`new global::A(source);`) instead of `[MapperConstructor]`. The bug is reproduced! The generated code is:

```
return new global::A(source);
```

Instead of the expected:
```
var target = new global::A();
target.Value = source.Value;
return target;
```

Now let me implement the fix. The issue is in `CtorMappingBuilder.TryBuildMapping`. When there's a copy constructor and `UseDeepCloning` is enabled, it should check if `[MapperConstructor]` is present on any other constructor, and if so, skip the copy constructor.

